    <h1 class="heading1">Maternity Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, we understand that pregnancy is a special journey, and we are dedicated to providing exceptional care and support to expectant mothers and their families. Our Maternity Department offers comprehensive maternity services, including prenatal care, labor and delivery, postpartum care, and breastfeeding support, ensuring a safe and memorable childbirth experience for every mother and baby.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Prenatal Care</h4>
            <p>We provide comprehensive prenatal care to monitor the health and well-being of expectant mothers throughout pregnancy. Our obstetricians offer regular check-ups, prenatal screenings, ultrasounds, and health education to promote a healthy pregnancy and address any concerns or complications that may arise.</p>

            <h4>Childbirth Education</h4>
            <p>We offer childbirth education classes and resources to help expectant parents prepare for labor, delivery, and parenthood. Our classes cover topics such as childbirth techniques, pain management options, breastfeeding basics, newborn care, and postpartum recovery, empowering parents to make informed decisions and feel confident during the childbirth process.</p>

            <h4>Labor and Delivery</h4>
            <p>Our Maternity Department features state-of-the-art labor and delivery suites equipped with advanced technology and amenities to ensure a comfortable and safe birthing experience. Our experienced obstetricians, nurses, and support staff provide personalized care, emotional support, and medical interventions as needed to support mothers through labor and childbirth.</p>

            <h4>Postpartum Care</h4>
            <p>We offer comprehensive postpartum care to support new mothers in their recovery and adjustment to motherhood. Our healthcare team provides postpartum check-ups, breastfeeding assistance, emotional support, and resources for postpartum depression screening and treatment, ensuring that mothers receive the care and support they need during the postpartum period.</p>

            <h4>Newborn Care</h4>
            <p>We provide expert care for newborns, including newborn screenings, vaccinations, and guidance on newborn care and feeding. Our maternity nurses and lactation consultants offer breastfeeding support, newborn care education, and assistance with bonding and attachment, helping new parents feel confident in caring for their newborn.</p>

            <h4>Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU)</h4>
            <p>For babies who require specialized medical care, our Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU) offers advanced neonatal care and support services. Our NICU is staffed by neonatologists, neonatal nurses, and respiratory therapists trained in caring for premature infants, low birth weight babies, and newborns with medical conditions or complications, ensuring the best possible outcomes for our tiniest patients.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
        <div class="cl">
            <h3>Family-Centered Care</h3>
            <p>At Aatura Hospital, we believe in family-centered care and strive to involve families in every step of the maternity journey. We encourage partner involvement in prenatal care, labor support, and newborn care, fostering bonding and support for the entire family unit. Our Maternity Department provides a warm, welcoming, and supportive environment where families can celebrate the arrival of their newest member.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content3">
        <div class="cl">
            <h3>Contact Us</h3>
            <p>If you are expecting a baby or planning to start a family, we invite you to contact our Maternity Department to learn more about our services and schedule a tour of our maternity facilities. Our dedicated team of obstetricians, nurses, and support staff is here to provide personalized care and support for you and your growing family.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

